                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d814">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.76/99: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-15T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 15, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>336. Federal Communications Commission states that station HKG5, Medellfn, using
                    A–2 emission, has been causing destructive interference for the past 3 months to
                    the eastern seaboard operations of the American Airlines, Inc. on the
                    aeronautical frequency 3257.5 kc.</p>
                <p>The United States enjoys definite priority rights to 3257.5 kc while HKG5 is not
                    registered for the frequency in the List of Frequencies of the Bureau of
                    International Telecommunications Union.</p>
                <p>Please take matter up with appropriate Colombian authorities with the request
                    that steps be taken to eliminate the interference complained of and advise
                    Department of result of your representations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
